sonusNodeMIB.description: The MIB Module for Node Management.

sonusNodeAdmnShelves.name: sonusNodeAdmnShelves
sonusNodeAdmnShelves.description: The number of shelves configured to be present in this node.

sonusNodeStatShelvesPresent.name: sonusNodeStatShelvesPresent
sonusNodeStatShelvesPresent.description: The number of shelves currently present in this node.

sonusNodeStatNextIfIndex.name: sonusNodeStatNextIfIndex
sonusNodeStatNextIfIndex.description: This MIB object identifies the next ifIndex to use in the creation of an interface. This MIB object directly corresponds to the ifIndex MIB object in the ifTable. A value of 0 means that no next ifIndex is currently available.

sonusNodeStatMgmtStatus.name: sonusNodeStatMgmtStatus
sonusNodeStatMgmtStatus.description: Identifies if this node can be effectively managed by a network management system. A value of 'manageable' indicates that it can be; the other values indicate that a significant operation is in progress and that a network management system should minimize any requests of this node.

sonusNodeShelfAdmnTable.name: sonusNodeShelfAdmnTable
sonusNodeShelfAdmnTable.description: This table contains information about each shelf which is configured to be a member of the node. This table describes the configured characteristics of each shelf, including the shelve's identity (sonusNodeShelfAdmnIpaddr1 and sonusNodeShelfAdmnIpaddr2). A row must be created by the manager for every slave shelf that is to join the master shelf as part of the node. Slave shelves which do not have correct entries in this table, can not join the node. A management entity may create rows for shelves that are anticipated to join the node in the future.

sonusNodeShelfAdmnEntry.name: sonusNodeShelfAdmnEntry
sonusNodeShelfAdmnEntry.description: This table describes the shelves that are configured as members of the GSX9000 Switch node.

sonusNodeShelfAdmnIndex.name: sonusNodeShelfAdmnIndex
sonusNodeShelfAdmnIndex.description: Identifies the target shelf in the node. Each node may be compprised of one or more shelves. The maximum number of shelves allowed in a node is six.

sonusNodeShelfAdmnState.name: sonusNodeShelfAdmnState
sonusNodeShelfAdmnState.description: The configured state of the target shelf in the node.

sonusNodeShelfAdmnIpaddr1.name: sonusNodeShelfAdmnIpaddr1
sonusNodeShelfAdmnIpaddr1.description: The IP Address of the shelf. This value identifies the shelf that may join the node. Each shelf has two IP addresses that it may be reached by. This is the first of those two addresses. Note that it is not possible to change this object on the master shelf. That would be tantamount to changing that shelf's IP address.

sonusNodeShelfAdmnIpaddr2.name: sonusNodeShelfAdmnIpaddr2
sonusNodeShelfAdmnIpaddr2.description: The IP Address of the shelf. This value identifies the shelf that may join the node. Each shelf has two IP addresses that it may be reached by. This is the second of those two addresses. Note that it is not possible to change this object on the master shelf. That would be tantamount to changing the shelf's IP address.

sonusNodeShelfAdmn48VdcAState.name: sonusNodeShelfAdmn48VdcAState
sonusNodeShelfAdmn48VdcAState.description: The configured state of the shelf's 48 VDC A-power supply. Indicates whether the A supply SHOULD be present. This object is not capable of disabling a connected supply.

sonusNodeShelfAdmn48VdcBState.name: sonusNodeShelfAdmn48VdcBState
sonusNodeShelfAdmn48VdcBState.description: The configured state of the shelf's 48 VDC B-power supply. Indicates whether the B supply SHOULD be present. This object is not capable of disabling a connected supply.

sonusNodeShelfAdmnStatus.name: sonusNodeShelfAdmnStatus
sonusNodeShelfAdmnStatus.description: The status of the indexed shelf in the GSX9000 node. If the value of this object is not accepted(3) or shuttingDown(4), then the objects in Sonus Shelf Status table are unavailable. The value of this object does not reach accepted(3) until after the slave shelf has contacted the master shelf, and has successfully joined the node. A value of shuttingDown(4) indicates the shelf will be unavailable shortly.

sonusNodeShelfAdmnRestart.name: sonusNodeShelfAdmnRestart
sonusNodeShelfAdmnRestart.description: This object is used to reset a shelf in the node. The object causes the management servers on the indexed shelf to perform the indicated operation. The restart(2) operation causes the management servers to reboot. The shutdown(3) operation causes the management servers to disable power to all cards on the indexed shelf, including themselves. The shutdown(3) operation requires physical intervention to re-power the shelf. This object always reads as unknown(1).

sonusNodeShelfAdmnRowStatus.name: sonusNodeShelfAdmnRowStatus
sonusNodeShelfAdmnRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status for this table.

sonusNodeShelfStatTable.name: sonusNodeShelfStatTable
sonusNodeShelfStatTable.description: This table contains status information about each shelf in the GSX9000 Switch node. Shelves within the node can can be configured before they are physically attached to the node. Shelves that are attached may not be powered or correctly configured as a slave. Therefore, it is possible that a slave shelf can not be detected, and is absent. The value of sonusNodeShelfAdmnStatus indicates the availability of this shelf. If the sonusNodeShelfAdmnStatus value for the index shelf does not indicate a status value of 'accepted', then this status table is not available.

sonusNodeShelfStatEntry.name: sonusNodeShelfStatEntry
sonusNodeShelfStatEntry.description: This table describes the shelves that are configured as members of the GSX9000 Switch node.

sonusNodeShelfStatIndex.name: sonusNodeShelfStatIndex
sonusNodeShelfStatIndex.description: Identifies the target shelf within the node. Returns the same value as sonusNodeShelfStatIndex, the index into this instance.

sonusNodeShelfStatSlots.name: sonusNodeShelfStatSlots
sonusNodeShelfStatSlots.description: The number of physical slots present in this shelf.

sonusNodeShelfStatSerialNumber.name: sonusNodeShelfStatSerialNumber
sonusNodeShelfStatSerialNumber.description: Identifies the Sonus serial number for this shelf.

sonusNodeShelfStatType.name: sonusNodeShelfStatType
sonusNodeShelfStatType.description: Identifies the Sonus shelf type. A shelf may be either the master shelf for the node, or it may be one of several slave shelves in the node. Every node contains exactly one master shelf. The master shelf in the management focal point for the node.

sonusNodeShelfStatFan.name: sonusNodeShelfStatFan
sonusNodeShelfStatFan.description: Identifies the status of the shelf's fan tray. A controllerFailure(2) indicates that the fan status can not be obtained. In that case in can not be determined if the fans are operational, or experiencing other failures as well.

sonusNodeShelfStat48VAStatus.name: sonusNodeShelfStat48VAStatus
sonusNodeShelfStat48VAStatus.description: The status of the shelf's 48 VDC A-power supply.

sonusNodeShelfStat48VBStatus.name: sonusNodeShelfStat48VBStatus
sonusNodeShelfStat48VBStatus.description: The status of the shelf's 48 VDC B-power supply.

sonusNodeShelfStatBackplane.name: sonusNodeShelfStatBackplane
sonusNodeShelfStatBackplane.description: The hardware type ID of the backplane in this shelf.

sonusNodeShelfStatBootCount.name: sonusNodeShelfStatBootCount
sonusNodeShelfStatBootCount.description: Specifies the number of times that this shelf has been booted. The boot count is specified from the perspective of the active management module running in the indexed shelf.

sonusNodeShelfStatTemperature.name: sonusNodeShelfStatTemperature
sonusNodeShelfStatTemperature.description: Indicates the temperature being sensed at this shelf's intake manifold. The temperature is indicated in Celcius.

sonusNodeShelfStatFanSpeed.name: sonusNodeShelfStatFanSpeed
sonusNodeShelfStatFanSpeed.description: Indicates the speed of the fan.

sonusNodeSrvrAdmnTable.name: sonusNodeSrvrAdmnTable
sonusNodeSrvrAdmnTable.description: The server module ADMN table describes the configuration of each server module slot in an indexed shelf. A slot in a shelf, MUST be configured to accept a particular server module HWTYPE. If the wrong type of server module is detected in the slot, that server module will not be allowed to complete its boot process. All server modules are held in the RESET state until that server module's state is set to ENABLED. A server module must have its state set to DISABLED, before the row can be deleted. The row must be deleted, and re-created in order to change the HWTYPE of the row. The server module mode must be set to OUTOFSERVICE before the row's state can be set to DISABLED. Deleting a row in this table, clears the server module hardware type association for this slot. THIS IS A MAJOR CONFIGURATION CHANGE. All configured parameters associated with this slot are permanently lost when the server module is deleted. A server module can not be deleted, until it's state has been set to DISABLED. A row's default value for state is DISABLED. The server module located in the slot is immediately placed in reset when its state is set to disabled.

sonusNodeSrvrAdmnShelfIndex.name: sonusNodeSrvrAdmnShelfIndex
sonusNodeSrvrAdmnShelfIndex.description: Identifies the target shelf. Returns the same value as sonusNodeShelfStatIndex, which was used to index into this table.

sonusNodeSrvrAdmnSlotIndex.name: sonusNodeSrvrAdmnSlotIndex
sonusNodeSrvrAdmnSlotIndex.description: Identifies the target slot within the shelf.

sonusNodeSrvrAdmnHwType.name: sonusNodeSrvrAdmnHwType
sonusNodeSrvrAdmnHwType.description: Identifies the type of server module the indexed slot has been configured to accept. Server modules other than this type are rejected by the System Manager. This object is required to create a row instance.

sonusNodeSrvrAdmnState.name: sonusNodeSrvrAdmnState
sonusNodeSrvrAdmnState.description: A server module must be enabled before System Manager will fully recognize it. The server module must be disabled before the server module can be deleted.

sonusNodeSrvrAdmnMode.name: sonusNodeSrvrAdmnMode
sonusNodeSrvrAdmnMode.description: A server module which is outOfService will not accept new calls. When taken out of service, its active calls may either be dried up or terminated, depending on the action specified. Server modules are created with a mode of inService. A server module must be outOfService in order to change its state to disabled.

sonusNodeSrvrAdmnAction.name: sonusNodeSrvrAdmnAction
sonusNodeSrvrAdmnAction.description: The type of action to perform when a server module is taken out of service. The active calls on the server module can be dried up for a specified dryup limit, or they can be forced to be terminated.

sonusNodeSrvrAdmnDryupLimit.name: sonusNodeSrvrAdmnDryupLimit
sonusNodeSrvrAdmnDryupLimit.description: Server module dryup limit, specified in minutes. If the server module has not dried up by the time this limit expires, the remaining active calls are abruptly terminated. A dryup limit of zero indicates that the system will wait forever for the dryup to complete.

sonusNodeSrvrAdmnDumpState.name: sonusNodeSrvrAdmnDumpState
sonusNodeSrvrAdmnDumpState.description: Indicates if a server module will create a crashblock file when a critical error which prevents the module from continuing, has occured.

sonusNodeSrvrAdmnRowStatus.name: sonusNodeSrvrAdmnRowStatus
sonusNodeSrvrAdmnRowStatus.description: Deleting a server module will place that slot in reset. All configuration parameters associated with the server module in this slot are destroyed.

sonusNodeSrvrAdmnRedundancyRole.name: sonusNodeSrvrAdmnRedundancyRole
sonusNodeSrvrAdmnRedundancyRole.description: Specifies the redundancy role this server module will play. This object is required to create a row instance.

sonusNodeSrvrAdmnAdapHwType.name: sonusNodeSrvrAdmnAdapHwType
sonusNodeSrvrAdmnAdapHwType.description: Identifies the type of adapter module the indexed slot has been configured to accept. Adapter modules other than this type are rejected by the System Manager. This object is required to create a row instance.

sonusNodeSrvrAdmnSpecialFunction.name: sonusNodeSrvrAdmnSpecialFunction
sonusNodeSrvrAdmnSpecialFunction.description: Specifies the logical function for this server module. This object may be specified only at row creation time, but is not required. If not specified, an appropriate default value will be assigned based on the server and adapter hardware types. A value of default(1) is not accepted or used.

sonusNodeSlotShelfIndex.name: sonusNodeSlotShelfIndex
sonusNodeSlotShelfIndex.description: Identifies the indexed shelf. Returns the same value as sonusNodeShelfStatIndex, which is used to index into this table.

sonusNodeSlotIndex.name: sonusNodeSlotIndex
sonusNodeSlotIndex.description: Identifies the indexed slot within the shelf.

sonusNodeSlotState.name: sonusNodeSlotState
sonusNodeSlotState.description: Identifies the operational state of the indexed slot in the shelf.

sonusNodeSlotHwType.name: sonusNodeSlotHwType
sonusNodeSlotHwType.description: Identifies the hardware type of the server module which was detected in the slot. Valid only if the sonusNodeSlotState is greater than inserted(2).

sonusNodeSlotHwTypeRev.name: sonusNodeSlotHwTypeRev
sonusNodeSlotHwTypeRev.description: Identifies the hardware type revision of the server module which was detected in the slot. Valid only if the sonusNodeSlotState is greater than inserted(2).

sonusNodeSlotPower.name: sonusNodeSlotPower
sonusNodeSlotPower.description: Identifies the server modules power mode. If the slot state is empty, the power status is unknown(1).

sonusNodeSlotAdapState.name: sonusNodeSlotAdapState
sonusNodeSlotAdapState.description: Identifies the adapter state of the indexed slot in the shelf.

sonusNodeSlotAdapHwType.name: sonusNodeSlotAdapHwType
sonusNodeSlotAdapHwType.description: Identifies the hardware type of the adapter module which was detected in the slot. Valid only if the sonusNodeSlotAdapState is present(3).

sonusNodeSrvrStatTable.name: sonusNodeSrvrStatTable
sonusNodeSrvrStatTable.description: The node server status table describes the status of the indexed server module in the node. This table is unavailable if the sonusNodeShelfStatStatus object indicates that this slot is empty. If the sonusNodeSrvrStatType object returns either 'absent' or 'unknown' the value of all other objects within this table are indeterministic.

sonusNodeSrvrStatShelfIndex.name: sonusNodeSrvrStatShelfIndex
sonusNodeSrvrStatShelfIndex.description: Identifies the target shelf. Returns the same value as sonusNodeShelfStatIndex, which was used to index into this table.

sonusNodeSrvrStatSlotIndex.name: sonusNodeSrvrStatSlotIndex
sonusNodeSrvrStatSlotIndex.description: Identifies the target slot within the shelf.

sonusNodeSrvrStatMiddVersion.name: sonusNodeSrvrStatMiddVersion
sonusNodeSrvrStatMiddVersion.description: Identifies the version of the MIDD EEPROM on this server module.

sonusNodeSrvrStatHwType.name: sonusNodeSrvrStatHwType
sonusNodeSrvrStatHwType.description: Identifies the type of server module in the indexed slot.

sonusNodeSrvrStatSerialNum.name: sonusNodeSrvrStatSerialNum
sonusNodeSrvrStatSerialNum.description: Identifies the serial number of the server module. This is the serial number assigned to the server module at manufacture.

sonusNodeSrvrStatPartNum.name: sonusNodeSrvrStatPartNum
sonusNodeSrvrStatPartNum.description: Identifies the part number of the module. This is the part number assigned to the module at manufacture.

sonusNodeSrvrStatPartNumRev.name: sonusNodeSrvrStatPartNumRev
sonusNodeSrvrStatPartNumRev.description: Identifies the manufacture part number revision level of the server module.

sonusNodeSrvrStatMfgDate.name: sonusNodeSrvrStatMfgDate
sonusNodeSrvrStatMfgDate.description: The date this server module assembly was manufactured.

sonusNodeSrvrStatFlashVersion.name: sonusNodeSrvrStatFlashVersion
sonusNodeSrvrStatFlashVersion.description: Identifies the version of the firmware within the non-volatile FLASH device on this server module.

sonusNodeSrvrStatSwVersion.name: sonusNodeSrvrStatSwVersion
sonusNodeSrvrStatSwVersion.description: Identifies the version of the runtime software application this is currently executing on this server module.

sonusNodeSrvrStatBuildNum.name: sonusNodeSrvrStatBuildNum
sonusNodeSrvrStatBuildNum.description: Identifies the build number of this software version.

sonusNodeSrvrStatMode.name: sonusNodeSrvrStatMode
sonusNodeSrvrStatMode.description: Identifies the operational status of the module in the indexed slot.

sonusNodeSrvrStatTemperature.name: sonusNodeSrvrStatTemperature
sonusNodeSrvrStatTemperature.description: Indicates the current Celcius temperature being sensed by the server module in the indexed slot.

sonusNodeSrvrStatMemUtilization.name: sonusNodeSrvrStatMemUtilization
sonusNodeSrvrStatMemUtilization.description: The current memory utilization of this server module. The value returned is a number from 0 to 100, representing the percentage of memory utilization. Note that this number can be somewhat misleading as many data structures are pre-allocated to ensure that the server modules maximum load capacity can be acheived and maintained. This may result is relatively high memory utilizations under fairly low load.

sonusNodeSrvrStatCpuUtilization.name: sonusNodeSrvrStatCpuUtilization
sonusNodeSrvrStatCpuUtilization.description: The current CPU utilization of this server module. The value returned is a number from 0 to 100, representing the percentage of CPU utilization.

sonusNodeSrvrStatHwTypeRev.name: sonusNodeSrvrStatHwTypeRev
sonusNodeSrvrStatHwTypeRev.description: The hardware type revision number of this server module.

sonusNodeSrvrStatSwVersionCode.name: sonusNodeSrvrStatSwVersionCode
sonusNodeSrvrStatSwVersionCode.description: Octet string that identifies the version of the runtime software application that is currently executing on this server module: Byte(s) Code ------- ---- 0 major version 1 minor version 2 release version 3 type (1:alpha, 2:beta, 3:release, 4:special) 4-5 type number

sonusNodeSrvrStatEpldRev.name: sonusNodeSrvrStatEpldRev
sonusNodeSrvrStatEpldRev.description: The EPLD revision level of this server module. An overall number which represents the total level of the server module.

sonusNodeSrvrStatHostName.name: sonusNodeSrvrStatHostName
sonusNodeSrvrStatHostName.description: Identifies the host name that software load of this module had been built on.

sonusNodeSrvrStatUserName.name: sonusNodeSrvrStatUserName
sonusNodeSrvrStatUserName.description: Identifies the user who builds software load of this module.

sonusNodeSrvrStatViewName.name: sonusNodeSrvrStatViewName
sonusNodeSrvrStatViewName.description: Identifies the viewName used for software build.

sonusNodeSrvrStatTotalMem.name: sonusNodeSrvrStatTotalMem
sonusNodeSrvrStatTotalMem.description: Indicates the total memory size of the server module.

sonusNodeSrvrStatFreeMem.name: sonusNodeSrvrStatFreeMem
sonusNodeSrvrStatFreeMem.description: Indicates the total memory available on the server module.

sonusNodeSrvrStatTotalSharedMem.name: sonusNodeSrvrStatTotalSharedMem
sonusNodeSrvrStatTotalSharedMem.description: Indicates the total shared memory size of the server module.

sonusNodeSrvrStatFreeSharedMem.name: sonusNodeSrvrStatFreeSharedMem
sonusNodeSrvrStatFreeSharedMem.description: Indicates the total shared memory available on the server module.

sonusNodeAdapStatTable.name: sonusNodeAdapStatTable
sonusNodeAdapStatTable.description: The node adapter status table describes the status of the indexed adapter module in the node. This table is unavailable if the sonusNodeSlotAdapState object indicates that this slot is unknown, empty or faulted.

sonusNodeAdapStatSlotIndex.name: sonusNodeAdapStatSlotIndex
sonusNodeAdapStatSlotIndex.description: Identifies the target slot within the shelf.

sonusNodeAdapStatMiddVersion.name: sonusNodeAdapStatMiddVersion
sonusNodeAdapStatMiddVersion.description: Identifies the version of the MIDD EEPROM on this adapter module.

sonusNodeAdapStatHwType.name: sonusNodeAdapStatHwType
sonusNodeAdapStatHwType.description: Identifies the type of adapter module in the indexed slot.

sonusNodeAdapStatHwTypeRev.name: sonusNodeAdapStatHwTypeRev
sonusNodeAdapStatHwTypeRev.description: Identifies the hardware type revision of the adapter module detected in the slot.

sonusNodeAdapStatSerialNum.name: sonusNodeAdapStatSerialNum
sonusNodeAdapStatSerialNum.description: Identifies the serial number of the adapter module. This is the serial number assigned to the card at manufacture.

sonusNodeAdapStatPartNum.name: sonusNodeAdapStatPartNum
sonusNodeAdapStatPartNum.description: Identifies the part number of the adapter module. This is the part number assigned to the card at manufacture.

sonusNodeAdapStatPartNumRev.name: sonusNodeAdapStatPartNumRev
sonusNodeAdapStatPartNumRev.description: Identifies the assembly revision level of the adapter module.

sonusNodeAdapStatMfgDate.name: sonusNodeAdapStatMfgDate
sonusNodeAdapStatMfgDate.description: The date this adapter module was manufactured.

sonusNodeSlotAdmnTable.name: sonusNodeSlotAdmnTable
sonusNodeSlotAdmnTable.description: The node slot admn table provides physical manipulation of a slot location in a shelf.

sonusNodeSlotAdmnSlotIndex.name: sonusNodeSlotAdmnSlotIndex
sonusNodeSlotAdmnSlotIndex.description: Identifies the target slot within the shelf.

sonusNodeSlotAdmnReset.name: sonusNodeSlotAdmnReset
sonusNodeSlotAdmnReset.description: Setting this object to reset(2) or coredump(3), will physically reset the server module installed in the indexed slot. This object always reads as undefined(1). This object bypasses all consistency and safety checks. This object is intended for evaluation testing.

sonusNvsConfigTable.name: sonusNvsConfigTable
sonusNvsConfigTable.description: This table specifies the Boot Parameters that apply only to the MNS present in the indexed shelf and slot. The Boot Parameters can only be accessed if the shelf is actively part of the node.

sonusBparamShelfIndex.name: sonusBparamShelfIndex
sonusBparamShelfIndex.description: Identifies the target shelf. This object returns the value of sonusNodeShelfStatIndex which was used to index into this table.

sonusBparamPasswd.name: sonusBparamPasswd
sonusBparamPasswd.description: The secure password which is used to access the Boot PROM menu subsystem. This object is not available through SNMP.

sonusBparamIpAddrSlot1Port0.name: sonusBparamIpAddrSlot1Port0
sonusBparamIpAddrSlot1Port0.description: The IP address assigned to the field service port. This port is not intended for customer use.

sonusBparamIpMaskSlot1Port0.name: sonusBparamIpMaskSlot1Port0
sonusBparamIpMaskSlot1Port0.description: The IP Address Mask assigned to the field service port.

sonusBparamIpGatewaySlot1Port0.name: sonusBparamIpGatewaySlot1Port0
sonusBparamIpGatewaySlot1Port0.description: The default IP Gateway address used by the field service port.

sonusBparamIfSpeedTypeSlot1Port0.name: sonusBparamIfSpeedTypeSlot1Port0
sonusBparamIfSpeedTypeSlot1Port0.description: The default link speed setting used by the field service port.

sonusBparamIpAddrSlot1Port1.name: sonusBparamIpAddrSlot1Port1
sonusBparamIpAddrSlot1Port1.description: The IP address assigned to management port number one.

sonusBparamIpMaskSlot1Port1.name: sonusBparamIpMaskSlot1Port1
sonusBparamIpMaskSlot1Port1.description: The IP address mask used by management port one.

sonusBparamIpGatewaySlot1Port1.name: sonusBparamIpGatewaySlot1Port1
sonusBparamIpGatewaySlot1Port1.description: The default IP Gateway address used by management port one.

sonusBparamIfSpeedTypeSlot1Port1.name: sonusBparamIfSpeedTypeSlot1Port1
sonusBparamIfSpeedTypeSlot1Port1.description: The default link speed setting used by management port one.

sonusBparamIpAddrSlot1Port2.name: sonusBparamIpAddrSlot1Port2
sonusBparamIpAddrSlot1Port2.description: The IP address assigned to management port number two.

sonusBparamIpMaskSlot1Port2.name: sonusBparamIpMaskSlot1Port2
sonusBparamIpMaskSlot1Port2.description: The IP address mask used by management port two.

sonusBparamIpGatewaySlot1Port2.name: sonusBparamIpGatewaySlot1Port2
sonusBparamIpGatewaySlot1Port2.description: The default gateway address used by management port two.

sonusBparamIfSpeedTypeSlot1Port2.name: sonusBparamIfSpeedTypeSlot1Port2
sonusBparamIfSpeedTypeSlot1Port2.description: The default link speed setting used by management port two.

sonusBparamIpAddrSlot2Port0.name: sonusBparamIpAddrSlot2Port0
sonusBparamIpAddrSlot2Port0.description: The IP address assigned to the field service port. This port is not intended for customer use.

sonusBparamIpMaskSlot2Port0.name: sonusBparamIpMaskSlot2Port0
sonusBparamIpMaskSlot2Port0.description: The IP Address Mask assigned to the field service port.

sonusBparamIpGatewaySlot2Port0.name: sonusBparamIpGatewaySlot2Port0
sonusBparamIpGatewaySlot2Port0.description: The default IP Gateway address used by the field service port.

sonusBparamIfSpeedTypeSlot2Port0.name: sonusBparamIfSpeedTypeSlot2Port0
sonusBparamIfSpeedTypeSlot2Port0.description: The default link speed setting used by the field service port.

sonusBparamIpAddrSlot2Port1.name: sonusBparamIpAddrSlot2Port1
sonusBparamIpAddrSlot2Port1.description: The IP address assigned to management port number one.

sonusBparamIpMaskSlot2Port1.name: sonusBparamIpMaskSlot2Port1
sonusBparamIpMaskSlot2Port1.description: The IP address mask used by management port one.

sonusBparamIpGatewaySlot2Port1.name: sonusBparamIpGatewaySlot2Port1
sonusBparamIpGatewaySlot2Port1.description: The default IP Gateway address used by management port one.

sonusBparamIfSpeedTypeSlot2Port1.name: sonusBparamIfSpeedTypeSlot2Port1
sonusBparamIfSpeedTypeSlot2Port1.description: The default link speed setting used by management port one.

sonusBparamIpAddrSlot2Port2.name: sonusBparamIpAddrSlot2Port2
sonusBparamIpAddrSlot2Port2.description: The IP address assigned to management port number two.

sonusBparamIpMaskSlot2Port2.name: sonusBparamIpMaskSlot2Port2
sonusBparamIpMaskSlot2Port2.description: The IP address mask used by management port two.

sonusBparamIpGatewaySlot2Port2.name: sonusBparamIpGatewaySlot2Port2
sonusBparamIpGatewaySlot2Port2.description: The default gateway address used by management port two.

sonusBparamIfSpeedTypeSlot2Port2.name: sonusBparamIfSpeedTypeSlot2Port2
sonusBparamIfSpeedTypeSlot2Port2.description: The default link speed setting used by management port two.

sonusBparamBootDelay.name: sonusBparamBootDelay
sonusBparamBootDelay.description: The amount of delay used to allow an administrator to gain access to the NVS configuration menus before the runtime software is loaded. The delay is specified in seconds. Increasing this delay, will increase the total system boot time by the same amount.

sonusBparamCoreState.name: sonusBparamCoreState
sonusBparamCoreState.description: Specifies whether core dumps are enabled. If core dumps are disabled, a fatal software fault will result in a reboot without the overhead of performing the core dump operation.

sonusBparamCoreLevel.name: sonusBparamCoreLevel
sonusBparamCoreLevel.description: Specifies the type of core dump behavior the shelf will display. Under normal(1) behavior, the server modules will execute a core dump only for fatal software errors. Under sensitive(2) behavior, the server modules will execute a core dump when the software recognizes a major, but non-fatal, software fault. Normal(1) is the strongly recommended setting.

sonusBparamBaudRate.name: sonusBparamBaudRate
sonusBparamBaudRate.description: The baud rate of a management port's physical interface.

sonusBparamNfsPrimary.name: sonusBparamNfsPrimary
sonusBparamNfsPrimary.description: The IP Address of the primary NFS Server for this switch.

sonusBparamNfsSecondary.name: sonusBparamNfsSecondary
sonusBparamNfsSecondary.description: The IP Address of the secondary NFS Server for this switch.

sonusBparamNfsMountPri.name: sonusBparamNfsMountPri
sonusBparamNfsMountPri.description: The NFS mount point exported by the Primary NFS server.

sonusBparamNfsMountSec.name: sonusBparamNfsMountSec
sonusBparamNfsMountSec.description: The NFS mount point exported by the Secondary NFS server.

sonusBparamNfsPathUpgrade.name: sonusBparamNfsPathUpgrade
sonusBparamNfsPathUpgrade.description: The name of the temporary load path override. This path is tried before the sonusBparamNfsPathLoad when specified. If the sonusBparamNfsPathUpgrade fails to completely boot the switch after three consecutive attempts, the path is automatically abandoned in favor of the sonusBparamNfsPathLoad.

sonusBparamNfsPathLoad.name: sonusBparamNfsPathLoad
sonusBparamNfsPathLoad.description: The directory, beneath the exported NFS mount point, which contains the switch's operational directories.

sonusBparamPrimName.name: sonusBparamPrimName
sonusBparamPrimName.description: The primary load file name for this server module.

sonusBparamSecName.name: sonusBparamSecName
sonusBparamSecName.description: The secondary load file name for this server module. The secondary file is tried when the primary file can not be opened or read.

sonusBparamMasterState.name: sonusBparamMasterState
sonusBparamMasterState.description: Specifies whether this shelf will participate in the node as a master shelf, or as a slave shelf. Each node contains exactly one master shelf, and may contain multiple slave shelves.

sonusBparamParamMode.name: sonusBparamParamMode
sonusBparamParamMode.description: Specifies the binary parameter file mode of the node. This mode specifies whether the node will attempt to load a binary parameter file. The paramMode can be set to disabled(1) which disables parameter file loading. The mode can be set to defaults(3), which temporarily disables binary parameter file loading, until after the next binary parameter file save cycle initiated by the runtime software. In both of these disabled cases, the node boots with default parameters and automatically loads and executes the CLI startup script. The paramMode may be set to binaryFile(2), which enables binary parameter file loading and disables the automatic CLI startup script loading. A binary parameter file must exist before the node can succesfully load a binary parameter file. The node will load default parameters when a valid parameter file can not be loaded. The node loads default parameters when either the parameter mode is set to disabled(1) or when the mode is set to defaults(3). When the mode is set to defaults(3), the mode is automatically updated to binaryFile(2) on the first parameter save cycle.

sonusBparamCliScript.name: sonusBparamCliScript
sonusBparamCliScript.description: The name of the CLI script which will be run automatically when the switch intentionally boots with default parameters. The switch will intentionally boot with default parameters when sonusBparamParamMode is set to either disabled(1) or defaults(3). This CLI script will never be run when the sonusBparamParamMode is set to binaryFile(2). If the script is not specified, or if it can not be located, it is not run. The switch expects to find the script file in the cli/sys directory, beneath the load path specified directory.

sonusBparamUId.name: sonusBparamUId
sonusBparamUId.description: The UNIX user ID used for all file accesses on both the primary and secondary NFS servers.

sonusBparamGrpId.name: sonusBparamGrpId
sonusBparamGrpId.description: The UNIX group ID used for all file accesses on both the primary and secondary NFS servers.

sonusBparamCoreDumpLimit.name: sonusBparamCoreDumpLimit
sonusBparamCoreDumpLimit.description: Indicates the maximum number of core dump files which can be created on behalf of a Server which is requesting a core dump. Setting the value to zero indicates no limit. This object is intended to limit the number of core dumps (and the amount of disk space used) when a Server repeatedly crashes.

sonusBparamNfsPathSoftware.name: sonusBparamNfsPathSoftware
sonusBparamNfsPathSoftware.description: The name of the software load path. This path is is appended to the Boot Path. This object may be NULL, in which case the software is loaded directly from the Boot Path. This object allows multiple revisions of software to be maintained below the Boot Path. This object can be overridden by the Upgrade Path object during a LSWU. During general operation the complete software load path is formed by concatenating this object to the Boot Path and any applicable file system mount point.

sonusFlashConfigTable.name: sonusFlashConfigTable
sonusFlashConfigTable.description: This table specifies the FLASH Update parameters for the indexed server module. The Boot Firmware for each server module is contained in the FLASH device. It is essential that once the upgrade process is initiated, that it be allowed to complete without interruption. Power loss or manually reseting the server module during the upgrade process will result in a loss of Boot Firmware.

sonusFlashAdmnShelfIndex.name: sonusFlashAdmnShelfIndex
sonusFlashAdmnShelfIndex.description: Identifies the target shelf within the node.

sonusFlashAdmnSlotIndex.name: sonusFlashAdmnSlotIndex
sonusFlashAdmnSlotIndex.description: Identifies the target slot within the shelf.

sonusFlashAdmnUpdateButton.name: sonusFlashAdmnUpdateButton
sonusFlashAdmnUpdateButton.description: Initiate the update of the specified server module's FLASH PROM now. This object always reads as the value update(1).

sonusFlashStatusTable.name: sonusFlashStatusTable
sonusFlashStatusTable.description: This table specifies the status of the FLASH Update process.

sonusFlashStatShelfIndex.name: sonusFlashStatShelfIndex
sonusFlashStatShelfIndex.description: Identifies the target shelf within the node.

sonusFlashStatSlotIndex.name: sonusFlashStatSlotIndex
sonusFlashStatSlotIndex.description: Identifies the target slot within the shelf.

sonusFlashStatState.name: sonusFlashStatState
sonusFlashStatState.description: The current state of the FLASH update process on the target server module.

sonusFlashStatLastStatus.name: sonusFlashStatLastStatus
sonusFlashStatLastStatus.description: The status of the last FLASH update that was executed.

sonusUserListNextIndex.name: sonusUserListNextIndex
sonusUserListNextIndex.description: The next valid index to use when creating a new sonusUserListEntry

sonusUserListTable.name: sonusUserListTable
sonusUserListTable.description: This table specifies the user access list for the node.

sonusUserListIndex.name: sonusUserListIndex
sonusUserListIndex.description: Identifies the target user list entry.

sonusUserListState.name: sonusUserListState
sonusUserListState.description: The administrative state of this user entry.

sonusUserListUserName.name: sonusUserListUserName
sonusUserListUserName.description: The user name of this user.

sonusUserListProfileName.name: sonusUserListProfileName
sonusUserListProfileName.description: The name of the profile applied to this user entry.

sonusUserListComment.name: sonusUserListComment
sonusUserListComment.description: A comment that is associated with this user.

sonusUserListAccess.name: sonusUserListAccess
sonusUserListAccess.description: The priviledge level of this user.

sonusUserListRowStatus.name: sonusUserListRowStatus
sonusUserListRowStatus.description: Row status object for this table.

sonusUserListStatusTable.name: sonusUserListStatusTable
sonusUserListStatusTable.description: This table specifies status of the user access list for the node.

sonusUserListStatusIndex.name: sonusUserListStatusIndex
sonusUserListStatusIndex.description: Identifies the target user list status entry.

sonusUserListStatusLastConfigChange.name: sonusUserListStatusLastConfigChange
sonusUserListStatusLastConfigChange.description: Octet string that identifies the GMT timestamp of last successful SET PDU from this CLI user. field octects contents range ----- ------- -------- ----- 1 1-2 year 0..65536 2 3 month 1..12 3 4 day 1..31 4 5 hour 0..23 5 6 minutes 0..59 6 7 seconds 0..59 7 8 deci-sec 0..9 * Notes: - the value of year is in network-byte order

sonusUserProfileNextIndex.name: sonusUserProfileNextIndex
sonusUserProfileNextIndex.description: The next valid index to use when creating an entry in the sonusUserProfileTable.

sonusUserProfileTable.name: sonusUserProfileTable
sonusUserProfileTable.description: This table specifies the user access list for the node.

sonusUserProfileName.name: sonusUserProfileName
sonusUserProfileName.description: The name of this user profile. This object is required to create the table entry.

sonusUserProfileUserState.name: sonusUserProfileUserState
sonusUserProfileUserState.description: The administrative state of this profiled user entry.

sonusUserProfileUserPasswd.name: sonusUserProfileUserPasswd
sonusUserProfileUserPasswd.description: The password for the profiled user entry.

sonusUserProfileUserComment.name: sonusUserProfileUserComment
sonusUserProfileUserComment.description: The comment that is associated with the profiled user entry.

sonusUserProfileUserAccess.name: sonusUserProfileUserAccess
sonusUserProfileUserAccess.description: The priviledge level of the profiled user entry.

sonusUserProfileUserCommentState.name: sonusUserProfileUserCommentState
sonusUserProfileUserCommentState.description: Indicates whether the sonusUserProfileUserComment object is present in this user profile.

sonusUserProfileUserPasswdState.name: sonusUserProfileUserPasswdState
sonusUserProfileUserPasswdState.description: Indicates whether the sonusUserProfileUserPasswd object is present in this user profile.

sonusUserProfileUserAccessState.name: sonusUserProfileUserAccessState
sonusUserProfileUserAccessState.description: Indicates whether the sonusUserProfileUserAccess object is present in this user profile.

sonusUserProfileUserStateState.name: sonusUserProfileUserStateState
sonusUserProfileUserStateState.description: Indicates whether the sonusUserProfileUserState object is present in this user profile.

sonusSwLoadTable.name: sonusSwLoadTable
sonusSwLoadTable.description: This table specifies the hardware type based software load table for the server modules in the node.

sonusSwLoadAdmnIndex.name: sonusSwLoadAdmnIndex
sonusSwLoadAdmnIndex.description: Identifies the target software load entry.

sonusSwLoadAdmnImageName.name: sonusSwLoadAdmnImageName
sonusSwLoadAdmnImageName.description: Identifies the name of the image to load for the hardware type identified by sonusSwLoadAdmnHwType.

sonusSwLoadAdmnHwType.name: sonusSwLoadAdmnHwType
sonusSwLoadAdmnHwType.description: Identifies the target hardware type for the load image. This object can only be written at row creation.

sonusSwLoadAdmnRowStatus.name: sonusSwLoadAdmnRowStatus
sonusSwLoadAdmnRowStatus.description: The RowStatus object for this row.

sonusSwLoadSpecTable.name: sonusSwLoadSpecTable
sonusSwLoadSpecTable.description: This table specifies the hardware type based software load table for the server modules in the node.

sonusSwLoadSpecAdmnShelfIndex.name: sonusSwLoadSpecAdmnShelfIndex
sonusSwLoadSpecAdmnShelfIndex.description: Identifies the target shelf for this load entry entry.

sonusSwLoadSpecAdmnSlotIndex.name: sonusSwLoadSpecAdmnSlotIndex
sonusSwLoadSpecAdmnSlotIndex.description: Identifies the target slot within the chassis for this load entry.

sonusSwLoadSpecAdmnImageName.name: sonusSwLoadSpecAdmnImageName
sonusSwLoadSpecAdmnImageName.description: Identifies the name of the image to load.

sonusSwLoadSpecAdmnRowStatus.name: sonusSwLoadSpecAdmnRowStatus
sonusSwLoadSpecAdmnRowStatus.description: The RowStatus object for this row.

sonusParamSaveSeqNumber.name: sonusParamSaveSeqNumber
sonusParamSaveSeqNumber.description: The parameter save sequence number assigned to this parameter file.

sonusParamSaveTimeStart.name: sonusParamSaveTimeStart
sonusParamSaveTimeStart.description: The system uptime, measured in milliseconds, when the last parameter save cycle started.

sonusParamSaveTimeStop.name: sonusParamSaveTimeStop
sonusParamSaveTimeStop.description: The system uptime, measured in milliseconds, when the last parameter save cycle ended.

sonusParamSaveDuration.name: sonusParamSaveDuration
sonusParamSaveDuration.description: The measured time in milliseconds to complete the last parameter save cycle.

sonusParamSaveTotalBytes.name: sonusParamSaveTotalBytes
sonusParamSaveTotalBytes.description: The number of bytes contained in the last binary parameter file saved.

sonusParamSaveTotalRecords.name: sonusParamSaveTotalRecords
sonusParamSaveTotalRecords.description: The number of individual parameter records contained in the last binary parameter file saved.

sonusParamSaveFilename.name: sonusParamSaveFilename
sonusParamSaveFilename.description: Identifies the name of the image to load for the hardware type identified by sonusSwLoadAdmnHwType.

sonusParamSaveState.name: sonusParamSaveState
sonusParamSaveState.description: The current state of the active Management Server's parameter saving process.

sonusParamLoadServer.name: sonusParamLoadServer
sonusParamLoadServer.description: The IP Address of the NFS server from which parameters were loaded from.

sonusParamLoadFileType.name: sonusParamLoadFileType
sonusParamLoadFileType.description: The type of binary parameter which was loaded. Under normal circumstances, the primary(1) parameter file will always be loaded. When default parameters are used, no parameter file is loaded, and the value none(4) is used for the file type.

sonusParamLoadStatus.name: sonusParamLoadStatus
sonusParamLoadStatus.description: Indicates the status of the last binary parameter file load. The value defaults(1) indicates that parameters were not loaded and that the node began with default parameters. The value success(2) indicates that a binary parameter file was successfully loaded when the node booted. The value paramError(3) indicates that the node attempted to load a binary parameter file and that there was an error in the processing of the file. The node may be running with a partial parameter file when this error is indicated.

sonusParamLoadSerialNum.name: sonusParamLoadSerialNum
sonusParamLoadSerialNum.description: Identifies the serial number of the node which created the parameter file loaded by this node.

sonusParamSavePrimarySrvrState.name: sonusParamSavePrimarySrvrState
sonusParamSavePrimarySrvrState.description: The current state of parameter saving to this NFS server.

sonusParamSavePrimarySrvrReason.name: sonusParamSavePrimarySrvrReason
sonusParamSavePrimarySrvrReason.description: The failure code associated with the last parameter save pass to this NFS server.

sonusParamSaveSecondarySrvrState.name: sonusParamSaveSecondarySrvrState
sonusParamSaveSecondarySrvrState.description: The current state of parameter saving to this NFS server.

sonusParamSaveSecondarySrvrReason.name: sonusParamSaveSecondarySrvrReason
sonusParamSaveSecondarySrvrReason.description: The failure code associated with the last parameter save pass to this NFS server.

sonusParamLastSaveTime.name: sonusParamLastSaveTime
sonusParamLastSaveTime.description: Octet string that identifies the GMT timestamp of last successful PIF write. field octects contents range ----- ------- -------- ----- 1 1-2 year 0..65536 2 3 month 1..12 3 4 day 1..31 4 5 hour 0..23 5 6 minutes 0..59 6 7 seconds 0..59 7 8 deci-sec 0..9 * Notes: - the value of year is in network-byte order

sonusParamAdmnMaxIncrPifs.name: sonusParamAdmnMaxIncrPifs
sonusParamAdmnMaxIncrPifs.description: The maximum of Incremental PIF files saved per NFS server

sonusNfsAdmnTable.name: sonusNfsAdmnTable
sonusNfsAdmnTable.description: This table specifies the configurable NFS options for each MNS in each shelf.

sonusNfsAdmnShelfIndex.name: sonusNfsAdmnShelfIndex
sonusNfsAdmnShelfIndex.description: Identifies the target shelf. This object returns the value of sonusNodeShelfStatIndex which was used to index into this table.

sonusNfsAdmnSlotIndex.name: sonusNfsAdmnSlotIndex
sonusNfsAdmnSlotIndex.description: Identifies the target MNS module slot within the shelf.

sonusNfsAdmnMountServer.name: sonusNfsAdmnMountServer
sonusNfsAdmnMountServer.description: Mounts the Primary or Secondary NFS server using mount parameters obtained from the NVS Boot parameters sonusBparamNfsPrimary or sonusBparamNfsSecondary, and sonusBparamNfsMountPri or sonusBparamNfsMountSec. Continuous retries will occur until the mount succeeds. This object is always read as noop(1).

sonusNfsAdmnUnmountServer.name: sonusNfsAdmnUnmountServer
sonusNfsAdmnUnmountServer.description: Unmounts the standby NFS server. Note: unmounting this server will disrupt any file I/O currently taking place on it. Continuous retries will occur until the unmount succeeds. This object is always read as noop(1).

sonusNfsAdmnToggleActiveServer.name: sonusNfsAdmnToggleActiveServer
sonusNfsAdmnToggleActiveServer.description: Toggles the Active NFS server between the Primary and Secondary, provided both servers are currently mounted. This object is always read as noop(1).

sonusNfsAdmnSetWritable.name: sonusNfsAdmnSetWritable
sonusNfsAdmnSetWritable.description: Clears the perception of a read-only condition on the Primary or Secondary NFS server, so that server will be considered viable as the Active server. This object is always read as noop(1).

sonusNfsStatTable.name: sonusNfsStatTable
sonusNfsStatTable.description: This table specifies NFS status objects for each MNS in each shelf.

sonusNfsStatShelfIndex.name: sonusNfsStatShelfIndex
sonusNfsStatShelfIndex.description: Identifies the target shelf. This object returns the value of sonusNodeShelfStatIndex which was used to index into this table.

sonusNfsStatSlotIndex.name: sonusNfsStatSlotIndex
sonusNfsStatSlotIndex.description: Identifies the target MNS module slot within the shelf.

sonusNfsStatPrimaryStatus.name: sonusNfsStatPrimaryStatus
sonusNfsStatPrimaryStatus.description: Indicates the mount status of the Primary NFS server: mounted and functioning properly, attemping to mount, indefinitely unmounted, attempting to unmount, mounted but read-only, testing connectivity, server failure, or invalid NFS parameters.

sonusNfsStatSecondaryStatus.name: sonusNfsStatSecondaryStatus
sonusNfsStatSecondaryStatus.description: Indicates the mount status of the Secondary NFS server: mounted and functioning properly, attemping to mount, indefinitely unmounted, attempting to unmount, mounted but read-only, testing connectivity, server failure, or invalid NFS parameters.

sonusNfsStatActiveServer.name: sonusNfsStatActiveServer
sonusNfsStatActiveServer.description: Indicates the current Active NFS server. This may change due to NFS failures or NFS administrative operations.

sonusNfsStatStandbyServer.name: sonusNfsStatStandbyServer
sonusNfsStatStandbyServer.description: Indicates the current Standby NFS server. This may change due to NFS failures or NFS administrative operations.

sonusNfsStatPrimaryIP.name: sonusNfsStatPrimaryIP
sonusNfsStatPrimaryIP.description: The IP Address of the currently mounted Primary NFS server. This may differ from the NVS settings if the user modified sonusBparamNfsPrimary without unmounting and remounting the Primary server.

sonusNfsStatSecondaryIP.name: sonusNfsStatSecondaryIP
sonusNfsStatSecondaryIP.description: The IP Address of the currently mounted Secondary NFS server. This may differ from the NVS settings if the user modified sonusBparamNfsSecondary without unmounting and remounting the Secondary server.

sonusNfsStatPrimaryMount.name: sonusNfsStatPrimaryMount
sonusNfsStatPrimaryMount.description: The mount point currently in use on the Primary NFS server. This may differ from the NVS settings if the user modified sonusBparamNfsMountPri without unmounting and remounting the Primary server.

sonusNfsStatSecondaryMount.name: sonusNfsStatSecondaryMount
sonusNfsStatSecondaryMount.description: The mount point currently in use on the Secondary NFS server. This may differ from the NVS settings if the user modified sonusBparamNfsMountSec without unmounting and remounting the Secondary server.

sonusNfsStatPrimaryLastError.name: sonusNfsStatPrimaryLastError
sonusNfsStatPrimaryLastError.description: Last consequential error received from the Primary NFS server. This object is reset to none(1) if the server is remounted.

sonusNfsStatSecondaryLastError.name: sonusNfsStatSecondaryLastError
sonusNfsStatSecondaryLastError.description: Last consequential error received from the Secondary NFS server. This object is reset to none(1) if the server is remounted.

sonusNfsServer.name: sonusNfsServer
sonusNfsServer.description: The NFS server referred to by the trap.

sonusNfsRole.name: sonusNfsRole
sonusNfsRole.description: Role assumed by the NFS server referred to by the trap.

sonusNfsServerIp.name: sonusNfsServerIp
sonusNfsServerIp.description: The IP address of the NFS server referred to by the trap.

sonusNfsServerMount.name: sonusNfsServerMount
sonusNfsServerMount.description: The mount point used on the NFS server referred to by the trap.

sonusNfsReason.name: sonusNfsReason
sonusNfsReason.description: The reason for the generation of the trap - administrative operation (mount, unmount, or toggle), server failure, server not writable, or server recovery.

sonusNodeShelfPowerA48VdcNormalNotificat.name: sonusNodeShelfPowerA48VdcNormalNotification
sonusNodeShelfPowerA48VdcNormalNotificat.description: A sonusShelfPowerA48VdcNormal trap indicates that 48V DC source A is operating normally for the specified shelf.

sonusNodeShelfPowerB48VdcNormalNotificat.name: sonusNodeShelfPowerB48VdcNormalNotification
sonusNodeShelfPowerB48VdcNormalNotificat.description: A sonusShelfPowerB48VdcNormal trap indicates that 48V DC source B is operating normally for the specified shelf.

sonusNodeShelfPowerA48VdcFailureNotifica.name: sonusNodeShelfPowerA48VdcFailureNotification
sonusNodeShelfPowerA48VdcFailureNotifica.description: A sonusShelfPowerA48VdcFailure trap indicates that 48V DC source A has failed for the specified shelf.

sonusNodeShelfPowerB48VdcFailureNotifica.name: sonusNodeShelfPowerB48VdcFailureNotification
sonusNodeShelfPowerB48VdcFailureNotifica.description: A sonusShelfPowerB48VdcFailure trap indicates that 48V DC source A has failed for the specified shelf.

sonusNodeShelfFanTrayFailureNotification.name: sonusNodeShelfFanTrayFailureNotification
sonusNodeShelfFanTrayFailureNotification.description: A sonusNodeShelfFanTrayFailure trap indicates that the fan controller on the specified shelf is indicating a problem. The Event Log should be examined for more detail. The fan tray should be replaced immediately.

sonusNodeShelfFanTrayOperationalNotifica.name: sonusNodeShelfFanTrayOperationalNotification
sonusNodeShelfFanTrayOperationalNotifica.description: A sonusNodeShelfFanTrayOperational trap indicates that the fan controller is fully operational on the specified shelf.

sonusNodeShelfFanTrayRemovedNotification.name: sonusNodeShelfFanTrayRemovedNotification
sonusNodeShelfFanTrayRemovedNotification.description: A sonusNodeShelfFanTrayRemoved trap indicates that the fan tray has been removed from the specified shelf. The fan tray should be replaced as soon as possible to avoid damage to the equipment as a result of overheating.

sonusNodeShelfFanTrayPresentNotification.name: sonusNodeShelfFanTrayPresentNotification
sonusNodeShelfFanTrayPresentNotification.description: A sonusNodeShelfFanTrayPresent trap indicates that a fan tray is present for the specified shelf.

sonusNodeShelfIntakeTempWarningNotificat.name: sonusNodeShelfIntakeTempWarningNotification
sonusNodeShelfIntakeTempWarningNotificat.description: A sonusNodeShelfIntakeTempWarning trap indicates that the intake temperature of the specified shelf has exceeded 45C degrees.

sonusNodeServerTempWarningNotification.name: sonusNodeServerTempWarningNotification
sonusNodeServerTempWarningNotification.description: A sonusNodeServerTempWarning trap indicates that the operating temperature of the specified shelf and slot has exceeded 60C degrees.

sonusNodeServerTempFailureNotification.name: sonusNodeServerTempFailureNotification
sonusNodeServerTempFailureNotification.description: A sonusNodeServerTempFailure trap indicates that the operating temperature of the specified shelf and slot has exceeded 70C degrees. A server module operating for any length of time at this temperature is in danger of being physically damaged. The specified module should be disabled and/or removed from the shelf.

sonusNodeServerTempNormalNotification.name: sonusNodeServerTempNormalNotification
sonusNodeServerTempNormalNotification.description: A sonusNodeServerTempNormal trap indicates that the operating temperature of the specified shelf and slot has is below 60C degrees.

sonusNodeServerInsertedNotification.name: sonusNodeServerInsertedNotification
sonusNodeServerInsertedNotification.description: A sonusNodeServerInserted trap indicates that a server module has been inserted in the specified shelf and slot.

sonusNodeServerRemovedNotification.name: sonusNodeServerRemovedNotification
sonusNodeServerRemovedNotification.description: A sonusNodeServerRemoved trap indicates that a server module has been removed from the specified shelf and slot.

sonusNodeServerResetNotification.name: sonusNodeServerResetNotification
sonusNodeServerResetNotification.description: A sonusNodeServerReset trap indicates that the server module in the specified shelf and slot has been reset.

sonusNodeServerOperationalNotification.name: sonusNodeServerOperationalNotification
sonusNodeServerOperationalNotification.description: A sonusNodeServerOperational trap indicates that the booting and initialization has completed successfully for the server module in the specified shelf and slot.

sonusNodeServerPowerFailureNotification.name: sonusNodeServerPowerFailureNotification
sonusNodeServerPowerFailureNotification.description: A sonusNodeServerPowerFailure trap indicates that a power failure has been detected for the server module in the specified shelf and slot.

sonusNodeServerSoftwareFailureNotificati.name: sonusNodeServerSoftwareFailureNotification
sonusNodeServerSoftwareFailureNotificati.description: A sonusNodeServerSoftwareFailure trap indicates that a software failure has occurred or the server module in the specified shelf and slot. The EventLog should be viewed for possible additional information.

sonusNodeServerHardwareFailureNotificati.name: sonusNodeServerHardwareFailureNotification
sonusNodeServerHardwareFailureNotificati.description: A sonusNodeServerHardwareFailure trap indicates that a hardware failure has occurred or the server module in the specified shelf and slot. The EventLog should be viewed for possible additional information.

sonusNodeAdapterInsertedNotification.name: sonusNodeAdapterInsertedNotification
sonusNodeAdapterInsertedNotification.description: A sonusNodeAdapterInserted trap indicates that an adapter module has been inserted in the specified shelf and slot.

sonusNodeAdapterRemovedNotification.name: sonusNodeAdapterRemovedNotification
sonusNodeAdapterRemovedNotification.description: A sonusNodeAdpaterRemoved trap indicates that an adapter module has been removed from the specified shelf and slot.

sonusNodeMtaInsertedNotification.name: sonusNodeMtaInsertedNotification
sonusNodeMtaInsertedNotification.description: A sonusNodeMtaInserted trap indicates that a Management Timing Adapter has been inserted in the specified shelf and slot.

sonusNodeMtaRemovedNotification.name: sonusNodeMtaRemovedNotification
sonusNodeMtaRemovedNotification.description: A sonusNodeMtaRemoved trap indicates that a Management Timing Adapter has been removed from the specified shelf and slot.

sonusNodeEthernetActiveNotification.name: sonusNodeEthernetActiveNotification
sonusNodeEthernetActiveNotification.description: A sonusNodeEthernetActive trap indicates that an Ethernet link is active for the specified shelf, slot and port.

sonusNodeEthernetInactiveNotification.name: sonusNodeEthernetInactiveNotification
sonusNodeEthernetInactiveNotification.description: A sonusNodeEthernetInactive trap indicates that an Ethernet link is inactive for the specified shelf, slot and port.

sonusNodeEthernetDegradedNotification.name: sonusNodeEthernetDegradedNotification
sonusNodeEthernetDegradedNotification.description: A sonusNodeEthernetDegraded trap indicates that an Ethernet link is detecting network errors for the specified shelf, slot and port. The EventLog should be viewed for possible additional information.

sonusNodeBootNotification.name: sonusNodeBootNotification
sonusNodeBootNotification.description: The Management Node Server module, in the node's master shelf, has begun the Node Boot process.

sonusNodeSlaveShelfBootNotification.name: sonusNodeSlaveShelfBootNotification
sonusNodeSlaveShelfBootNotification.description: The Management Node Server module, in a node's slave shelf, has begun the Node Boot process.

sonusNodeNfsServerSwitchoverNotification.name: sonusNodeNfsServerSwitchoverNotification
sonusNodeNfsServerSwitchoverNotification.description: Indicates that the Active NFS server has switched over to the Standby for the specified reason on the MNS in the given shelf and slot. The NFS server specified is the new Active.

sonusNodeNfsServerOutOfServiceNotificati.name: sonusNodeNfsServerOutOfServiceNotification
sonusNodeNfsServerOutOfServiceNotificati.description: Indicates that the NFS server specified went out-of-service for the reason provided on the MNS in the given shelf and slot. If it was the result of a server failure, the error that caused the failure is also specified.

sonusNodeNfsServerInServiceNotification.name: sonusNodeNfsServerInServiceNotification
sonusNodeNfsServerInServiceNotification.description: Indicates that the NFS server specified came in-service for the reason provided on the MNS in the given shelf and slot. The Active/Standby role assumed by the server is also provided.

sonusNodeNfsServerNotWritableNotificatio.name: sonusNodeNfsServerNotWritableNotification
sonusNodeNfsServerNotWritableNotificatio.description: Indicates that the NFS server specified is no longer writable by the MNS in the given shelf and slot. The error code received is provided.

sonusNodeServerDisabledNotification.name: sonusNodeServerDisabledNotification
sonusNodeServerDisabledNotification.description: The server modules administrative state has been set to disabled.

sonusNodeServerEnabledNotification.name: sonusNodeServerEnabledNotification
sonusNodeServerEnabledNotification.description: The server modules administrative state has been set to enabled.

sonusNodeServerDeletedNotification.name: sonusNodeServerDeletedNotification
sonusNodeServerDeletedNotification.description: The server module has been deleted from the node's configuration. All configuration data associated with the server module has been deleted.

sonusParamBackupLoadNotification.name: sonusParamBackupLoadNotification
sonusParamBackupLoadNotification.description: The backup parameter file was loaded. This indicates that the primary parameter file was lost or corrupted. The backup parameter file may contain data which is older than what the primary parameter file contains.

sonusParamCorruptionNotification.name: sonusParamCorruptionNotification
sonusParamCorruptionNotification.description: The binary parameter inspected was corrupted. The indicated file was skipped due to corruption. This trap is only transmitted if a valid backup parameter file is located and successfully loaded.

sonusNodeAdapterMissingNotification.name: sonusNodeAdapterMissingNotification
sonusNodeAdapterMissingNotification.description: A sonusNodeAdpaterMissing trap indicates that an adapter module has not been detected in a specific shelf and slot.

sonusNodeAdapterFailureNotification.name: sonusNodeAdapterFailureNotification
sonusNodeAdapterFailureNotification.description: A sonusNodeAdpaterFailure trap indicates that an adapter module has been detected but is not operational.

sonusNodeSlotResetNotification.name: sonusNodeSlotResetNotification
sonusNodeSlotResetNotification.description: A sonusNodeSlotReset trap indicates that a server module in the designated slot was reset.

sonusNodeParamWriteCompleteNotification.name: sonusNodeParamWriteCompleteNotification
sonusNodeParamWriteCompleteNotification.description: A sonusNodeParamWriteComplete trap indicates that NFS server successfully complete PIF write.

sonusNodeParamWriteErrorNotification.name: sonusNodeParamWriteErrorNotification
sonusNodeParamWriteErrorNotification.description: A sonusNodeParamWriteError trap indicates that error occured during PIF write.
